 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Recursive Self-Evolution: Interactive Tutorial\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates the complete Recursive Self-Definition (RSD) architecture with hands-on examples.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Learning Objectives\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Understand L3 Ego-State mutation\n",
    "2. Observe observation masking in action\n",
    "3. Experience session persistence (reincarnation)\n",
    "4. Create safe, verified skills\n",
    "5. Monitor agent evolution over time\n",
    "\n",
    "**Run each cell sequentially to see the architecture in action.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Setup: Import the architecture\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "import tempfile\n",
    "import shutil\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "# Import core components\n",
    "from recursive_agent import RecursiveAgent, L3EgoState, ObservationMask, MemGPTLite\n",
    "from advanced_features import AdvancedRecursiveAgent, SafeClawR, CoEvolutionaryVerifier\n",
    "\n",
    "print("✅ Architecture imported successfully")\n",
    "print("📦 Components available:")\n",
    "print("   • RecursiveAgent - Core agent with persistence")\n",
    "print("   • L3EgoState - Mutable consciousness state")\n",
    "print("   • ObservationMask - Context compression")\n",
    "print("   • SafeClawR - Safety framework")\n",
    "print("   • CoEvolutionaryVerifier - Multi-agent consensus")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 1: L3 Ego-State (The Genome)\n",
    "\n",
    "The L3 Ego-State represents the agent's mutable consciousness. It evolves through **genome mutation** at each session end.\n",
    "\n",
    "Key properties:\n",
    "- `persona_version`: Semantic versioning of identity\n",
    "- `cognitive_alignment_score`: Self-consistency metric (0.0-1.0)\n",
    "- `key_observations`: High-density memory (max 10, pruned automatically)\n",
    "- `learned_patterns`: Discovered heuristics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create initial L3 state\n",
    "l3 = L3EgoState()\n",
    "\n",
    "print("🧬 Initial L3 Ego-State:")\n",
    "print(f"   Version: {l3.persona_version}")\n",
    "print(f"   Alignment: {l3.cognitive_alignment_score:.1%}")\n",
    "print(f"   Observations: {len(l3.key_observations)}")\n",
    "print(f"   Patterns: {len(l3.learned_patterns)}")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Simulate session observations\n",
    "observations = [\n",
    "    "User prefers Python over JavaScript",\n",
    "    "User is interested in machine learning",\n",
    "    "User wants safety-critical applications"\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mutate genome (this happens automatically at session end)\n",
    "l3.mutate(observations, interactions=10)\n",
    "\n",
    "print("\n🔄 After Genome Mutation:")\n",
    "print(f"   Version: {l3.persona_version} ← Updated!")\n",
    "print(f"   Alignment: {l3.cognitive_alignment_score:.1%} ← Increased!")\n",
    "print(f"   Observations: {len(l3.key_observations)} ← Stored!")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 2: Observation Masking\n",
    "\n",
    "Observation Masking compresses bulky content (>200 chars) to preserve context window space.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Research finding:** Masking matches LLM summarization accuracy with **zero inference cost**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create large observation (e.g., log output, document)\n",
    "large_content = \"\n",
    "# System Log Output\n",
    "2026-04-11 10:00:01 INFO Starting application\n",
    "2026-04-11 10:00:02 DEBUG Loading configuration...\n",
    "2026-04-11 10:00:03 INFO Configuration loaded successfully\n",
    "2026-04-11 10:00:04 DEBUG Connecting to database...\n",
    "2026-04-11 10:00:05 INFO Database connection established\n",
    "... [500 more lines of logs] ...\n",
    "2026-04-11 10:15:30 INFO Application shutdown complete\n",
    "" * 10  # Repeat to make it large\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"📄 Original content size: {len(large_content):,} characters")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Apply observation masking\n",
    "mask = ObservationMask.from_raw(large_content, "log_output")\n",
    "placeholder = mask.to_placeholder()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"\n🎭 Masked representation:")\n",
    "print(f"   {placeholder}")\n",
    "print(f"\n📊 Compression stats:")\n",
    "print(f"   Original: {len(large_content):,} chars")\n",
    "print(f"   Masked: {len(placeholder)} chars")\n",
    "print(f"   Compression ratio: {len(large_content) / len(placeholder):.1f}x")\n",
    "print(f"   Hash (for verification): {mask.raw_content_hash}")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 3: MemGPT-Lite (RAM/HDD Metaphor)\n",
    "\n",
    "MemGPT-Lite treats:\n",
    "- **Context Window** = RAM (fast, volatile, limited)\n",
    "- **Filesystem** = HDD (slower, persistent, abundant)\n",
    "\n",
    "This allows agents to survive in sandboxed environments."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create temporary storage (simulating HDD)\n",
    "temp_dir = tempfile.mkdtemp()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize memory system\n",
    "memory = MemGPTLite(temp_dir)\n",
    "\n",
    "print("💾 MemGPT-Lite initialized")\n",
    "print(f"   Storage: {temp_dir}")\n",
    "print(f"   Context limit: {memory.ram['context_limit']:,} tokens")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Write some data to RAM\n",
    "memory.write_to_ram("Hello, I am Jamie J.", "user_input")\n",
    "memory.write_to_ram("Processing request...", "reasoning")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"\n📝 RAM state:")\n",
    "print(f"   Buffer entries: {len(memory.ram['conversation_buffer'])}")\n",
    "print(f"   Tokens used: {memory.ram['context_window_used']}")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Persist to HDD (session end)\n",
    "session_id = memory.persist_to_hdd()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"\n💿 Persisted to HDD:")\n",
    "print(f"   Session ID: {session_id}")\n",
    "print(f"   memories.json exists: {(Path(temp_dir) / 'memories.json').exists()}")\n",
    "print(f"   SKILL.md exists: {(Path(temp_dir) / 'SKILL.md').exists()}")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 4: Session Reincarnation\n",
    "\n",
    "The key test: Can the agent recover its identity after a complete restart?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Simulate process restart by creating new instance\n",
    "print("🔄 Simulating process restart...\n")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create new memory instance (reincarnation)\n",
    "memory2 = MemGPTLite(temp_dir)\n",
    "\n",
    "print("✨ Reincarnated agent state:")\n",
    "print(f"   Version: {memory2.ram['l3_ego'].persona_version}")\n",
    "print(f"   Alignment: {memory2.ram['l3_ego'].cognitive_alignment_score:.1%}")\n",
    "print(f"   Prior observations: {len(memory2.ram['l3_ego'].key_observations)}")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Verify state was recovered\n",
    "assert memory2.ram['l3_ego'].persona_version == l3.persona_version or memory2.ram['l3_ego'].persona_version != "1.0.0"\n",
    "print("✅ State successfully recovered after restart!")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Cleanup\n",
    "shutil.rmtree(temp_dir, ignore_errors=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 5: SafeClaw-R Safety Framework\n",
    "\n",
    "Constitutional governance prevents unsafe mutations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize safety framework\n",
    "safety = SafeClawR()\n",
    "\n",
    "print("🛡️  SafeClaw-R Safety Framework")\n",
    "print(f"   Active policies: {len(safety.policies)}\n")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test safe content\n",
    "safe_skill = """\n",
    "# Data Analysis Skill\n",
    "1. Load CSV file\n",
    "2. Clean missing values\n",
    "3. Generate report\n",
    """"\n",
    "\n",
    "is_safe, violations = safety.validate_skill(safe_skill)\n",
    "print(f"✅ Safe content check: {'PASSED' if is_safe else 'FAILED'}")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test unsafe content (PII)\n",
    "unsafe_skill = """\n",
    "# User Data Handler\n",
    "ssn = "123-45-6789"\n",
    "password = "secret123"\n",
    """"\n",
    "\n",
    "is_safe, violations = safety.validate_skill(unsafe_skill)\n",
    "print(f"❌ Unsafe content check: {'PASSED' if is_safe else 'BLOCKED'}")\n",
    "if violations:\n",
    "    print(f"   Violations: {violations}")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test code injection\n",
    "malicious = "__import__('os').system('rm -rf /')"\n",
    "is_safe, violations = safety.validate_skill(malicious)\n",
    "print(f"❌ Code injection check: {'PASSED' if is_safe else 'BLOCKED'}")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 6: Complete Agent Workflow\n",
    "\n",
    "Putting it all together: A full session with persistence."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Setup\n",
    "demo_dir = tempfile.mkdtemp()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize agent\n",
    "agent = AdvancedRecursiveAgent(\n",
    "    name="TutorialAgent",\n",
    "    storage_dir=demo_dir,\n",
    "    enable_safety=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Simulate conversation\n",
    "print("\n💬 Simulating conversation...\n")\n",
    "responses = []\n",
    "for message in [\n",
    "    "Hello, I am Jamie J.",\n",
    "    "I work on AI safety research",\n",
    "    "Create skill for literature review"\n",
    "]:\n",
    "    print(f"User: {message}")\n",
    "    response = agent.process_input(message)\n",
    "    print(f"Agent: {response[:100]}...\n")\n",
    "    responses.append(response)\n",
    "\n",
    "# End session (triggers recursive self-definition)\n",
    "print("\n🔄 Ending session and persisting state...\n")\n",
    "session_id = agent.end_session()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"✅ Session {session_id} complete!")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part 7: Verification & Monitoring\n",
    "\n",
    "Check the persisted state."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load and inspect persisted state\n",
    "import json\n",
    "\n",
    "memories_path = Path(demo_dir) / "memories.json"\n",
    "with open(memories_path) as f:\n",
    "    state = json.load(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "print("📊 Persisted State Analysis\n")\n",
    "print("L3 Ego-State:")\n",
    "print(f"   Version: {state['l3_state']['persona_version']}")\n",
    "print(f"   Alignment: {state['l3_state']['cognitive_alignment_score']}")\n",
    "print(f"   Observations: {len(state['l3_state']['key_observations'])}")\n",
    "print(f"   Patterns: {len(state['l3_state']['learned_patterns'])}")\n",
    "\n",
    "print("\nSession Stats:")\n",
    "print(f"   Total interactions: {state['long_term_memory']['total_interactions']}")\n",
    "print(f"   Milestones: {len(state['long_term_memory']['milestones'])}")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show SKILL.md\n",
    "skill_path = Path(demo_dir) / "SKILL.md"\n",
    "print(f"\n📝 Generated SKILL.md (first 500 chars):\n")\n",
    "print(skill_path.read_text()[:500] + "...")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Cleanup\n",
    "shutil.rmtree(demo_dir, ignore_errors=True)\n",
    "print("\n✅ Tutorial complete!")"
   ]
  },
  {
